SEO

Run & scale your business

Create Your Site
Learn more

Optimized robots.txt file

Your site's robots.txt file is already optimized to tell search engines which pages to crawl.

Structured data markup

Markup allows site content to be eligible for rich results. It's preset for some pages, like products and blog posts.

Server side rendering (SSR)

Wix’s infrastructure is based on SSR, allowing search engines to fully read your site content.

URL customization

Edit the URL slugs for site pages. Create consistency with variables and structure with site hierarchy.

SEO Meta Tags

Meta tags are automatically added to all pages so that search engines can display them properly.

Canonical tags

Wix automatically sets default canonical tags. Edit them to tell search engines which pages are primary versions for indexing.

Social sharing optimization

Customize your pages for social networks like Facebook and Pinterest by adding your own images, titles, and descriptions.

SEO settings

Customize the default page settings and meta tags across all page types at once with defaults, or edit them individually.

XML sitemaps

Wix automates your indexing with built-in individual sitemaps and IndexNow to help improve discoverability.

URL Redirect Manager

Create 301 redirects for individual pages and groups of pages on your site, and send traffic to new locations.

Bot log reports

Review your log data to get a better understanding of how search engine bots crawl your site.

CDN and caching

Wix integrates with external CDN providers allowing automatic caching, which enables faster site loading.

Image optimization

Wix automatically optimizes site images for quality, search, and faster downloads.

AMP for Wix blog

Get faster loading times on mobile devices for blog posts with AMP versions.

SEO APIs for developers

Customize your SEO tags from client-side code with Velo APIs.

Fast homepage indexing

Submit your sitemap and homepage for fast indexing by connecting to Google through the SEO Setup Checklist.

Google Business Profile

Bring in local traffic from search results with a Google Business Profile. Set up with Wix or import an existing one.

Site verification

Verify your site, confirm ownership, and track site performance in search results on Google, Bing, Yandex, Naver and Pinterest.

SEO setup checklist

Follow a personalized checklist of SEO setup tasks to help your site become more visible in online searches.

Tracking events

Automatically send events and track visitor behavior by connecting third-party marketing tools, like Google Analytics and more.

Wix Analytics

Get actionable insights to help you better understand and improve your site's SEO.

Site inspection tool

Learn how Google views your site and troubleshoot pages not appearing in search results.

Lumar (DeepCrawl) integration

Identify opportunities to improve your SEO by running technical audits on your site.

Semrush keyword research tool

Use this tool to find high-performing keywords to help boost your site's traffic.

SEO Assistant

Fix current issues and follow recommendations to improve your site’s performance in search results.

Customize default SEO settings

Customize the default page settings and meta tags across all page types to create structure and save time.

SEO Dashboard with GSC insights

Get access to site performance data on Google, SEO tools, and more directly from your SEO Dashboard.

Wix Studio’s enterprise solution allows large-scale businesses to deploy content quickly and manage a multi-site ecosystem from one centralized dashboard. Teams can build with robust no-code tools or advanced developer features, like open APIs to create custom experiences and easy integrations with the tools your business relies on—all on a powerful infrastructure for maximum security and reliability.
